@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Headings";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>Headings are block-level elements, and they come in six different rankings, <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> through <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>. Headings help to quickly break up content and establish hierarchy, and they are key identifiers for users reading a page. They also help search engines to index and determine the content on a page.</p>

    <p>Headings should be used in an order that is relevant to the content of a page. The primary heading of a page or section should be marked up with an <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> element, and subsequent headings should use <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h3&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h4&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h5&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> elements as necessary.</p>

    <p>Each heading level should be used where it is semantically valued, and should not be used to make text bold or big, there are other, better ways to do that.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-html">
&lt;h1&gt;Heading Level 1&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Heading Level 2&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Heading Level 3&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Heading Level 4&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Heading Level 5&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h6&gt;Heading Level 6&lt;/h6&gt;
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">Result</div>
        <div class="code-content result-preview">
            <h1>Heading Level 1</h1>
            <h2>Heading Level 2</h2>
            <h3>Heading Level 3</h3>
            <h4>Heading Level 4</h4>
            <h5>Heading Level 5</h5>
            <h6>Heading Level 6</h6>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("UsingTextBasedElements", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-outline-primary">← Using Text-Based Elements</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("Paragraphs", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-primary">Paragraphs →</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: var(--bs-body-bg);
    }

    h1 {
        color: var(--bs-heading-color);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    p {
        color: var(--bs-body-color);
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    code {
        font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
        background-color: #eef;
        padding: 2px 4px;
        border-radius: 3px;
    }

    .code-container {
        margin: 25px 0;
        border: 1px solid var(--bs-border-color);
        border-radius: 5px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    .code-header {
        background-color: #e9ecef;
        padding: 10px 15px;
        font-family: monospace;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #333;
    }

    .code-content {
        padding: 15px;
        overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .result-preview h1,
    .result-preview h2,
    .result-preview h3,
    .result-preview h4,
    .result-preview h5,
    .result-preview h6 {
        margin: 0 0 10px 0;
    }

    .navigation-buttons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .btn {
        padding: 8px 20px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: 500;
    }

    .btn-primary {
        background-color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
    }

    .btn-outline-primary {
        color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
    }
</style>
